
itools 0.62.3 (2010/10/01)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.i18n             itools.rss
  itools.core             itools.ical             itools.srx
  itools.csv              itools.log              itools.stl
  itools.database         itools.loop             itools.tmx
  itools.datatypes        itools.odf              itools.uri
  itools.fs               itools.office           itools.web
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.workflow
  itools.git              itools.pkg              itools.xliff
  itools.handlers         itools.python           itools.xml
  itools.html             itools.relaxng          itools.xmlfile
  itools.http             itools.rest

This release contains many bug fixes and small new features.

The 'get_handler' method (from itools.handlers) accepts the new 'soft'
parameter.  It defaults to 'False', so if the asked handler does not
exist an exception will be raised.  If set to 'True' and the handler
does not exist, the 'None' value will be returned.

There have been several improvements in different packages regarding
multilingual capabilities:

 (csv) explicit support for multilingual properties in the Table handler
 (gettext) the new utility function 'get_language_msg'
 (i18n) the 'format_number' function (still work-in-progess, see #1003)
 (web) handling multilingual fields using a suffix (e.g. 'title:en')

Other the bugs fixed:

 #987  (http) Context.load_body failed due to entity parsing error
 #1001 (html) support for autoplay in <embed> tag
 #1007 (csv)  table: allow "_" in parameter names
 #1008 (csv)  table: error with quoted parameters


